---
layout: base.njk
title: Templates
nav: templates
permalink: /templates/
---
<div class="ds-eyebrow">Starting points</div>
<h1 class="ds-title">Templates</h1>
<p class="ds-lede">Reusable page scaffolds — the "start here" layer. A consuming project copies one of these full pages instead of wiring the chrome by hand every time. Each composes real Curie components on the dark canvas using the layout primitives (<code>container</code>, <code>stack</code>, <code>grid</code>, <code>app-shell</code>, <code>appbar</code>). Open any one full-screen, then copy its markup.</p>

{% for t in templates %}
<h2 class="ds-section">{{ t.name }}</h2>
<p class="ds-meta-line">{{ t.purpose }}</p>
<div class="ds-template-frame">
  <iframe src="/templates/pages/{{ t.file }}" title="{{ t.name }} template" loading="lazy"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="ds-meta-line">Composes: {% for u in t.uses %}<code>{{ u }}</code>{% if not loop.last %} · {% endif %}{% endfor %}</div>
<div class="ds-meta-line"><a href="/templates/pages/{{ t.file }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open full page ↗</a> · source: <code>package/templates/{{ t.file }}</code></div>
{% endfor %}

<style>
  /* Live template preview: the iframe renders each page at the real column width
     (the templates are responsive), so it reads at full size — no tiny thumbnails.
     A scroll region shows the whole page without a giant fixed frame. */
  .ds-template-frame {
    width: 100%; height: 640px; margin: 14px 0 6px;
    border-radius: 16px; overflow: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-purple-card-border, #2d2850);
    background: var(--color-bg-primary, #140d2c);
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  }
  .ds-template-frame iframe { width: 100%; height: 1200px; border: 0; display: block; }
</style>
